  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This package is structurally identical to the base Morrison COU1 but is re-classified at Model Risk Level 3 to reflect the higher consequence of the tolerance decision. Twelve of the thirteen ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 factors are fully assessed and meet their required gradation levels. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' on the grounds that the validation experiment used the same CAD geometry as the simulation and therefore 'parameter equivalency does not apply'; however, the correct encoding for that determination would be 'not-applicable', not 'not-assessed'. At MRL 3 this omission materially weakens package credibility (W-EP-04).",
