      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that because the validation experiment and the production simulation share an identical CAD geometry and the same five nominal operating points, a formal equivalency analysis of input parameters does not apply to this COU. Consequently no gradation was assigned and the factor was left unassessed. Note: the technically correct encoding for a factor determined to be inapplicable would be factorStatus 'not-applicable'; the use of 'not-assessed' here constitutes the W-EP-04 weakness, because at Model Risk Level 3 every factor must be either assessed or formally scoped out."
